FBIS4-58578 "drnes087dd_94024" FBIS-NES-94-087 Daily Report 4 May 1994 Palestinian Affairs Fatah Dissident in Lebanon Calls 'Arafat Traitor Fatah Dissident in Lebanon Calls 'Arafat Traitor NC0505073294 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran in Arabic 1730 GMT 4 May 94 NC0505073294 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran Arabic BFN [Report by Beirut correspondent Muhammad Bishkar] [Text] Palestinian camps in Lebanon and Syria today observed a general strike to protest the signing of the self-rule agreement between the PLO and the Zionist enemy. A popular demonstration was staged in the Palestinian camp 'Ayn al-Hulwah in south Lebanon denouncing the agreement and describing the PLO leaders who signed it as traitors. Munir al-Maqdah, a Fatah Movement dissident in the camp, said Yasir 'Arafat has fallen in the trap and that he is now just a political refugee entrusted with putting down the Palestinian intifadah against occupation.
